Package: iLBA
Title: Information Loss Bounded Aggregation
Version: 1.0.0
Authors@R: 
    person("First", "Last", , "first.last@example.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides tools for constructing masked and aggregated frequency tables from microdata using the iLBA algorithm,
  especially in the presence of hierarchical variables. As demand grows-particularly in statistical agencies-for disseminating frequency tables based on various combinations of variables,
  including hierarchical structures, iLBA offers a masking method that enables safe public release by controlling disclosure risk 
  and information loss. This package provides aggregated and masked frequency tables based on user-specified variables, as well as full frequency tables with metadata.
  Moreover, it supports queries for masked frequency counts under specific conditions on selected variables.
